<TEXT>
stormie jones the worlds first heartliver 
transplant patient was upgraded to serious condition monday as she 
continued to recover from her second liver transplant 
stormie 12 of white settlement texas was moved from the 
intensive care unit of childrens hospital of pittsburgh to a 
regular hospital room 
shes doing well she regaining her strength quickly said 
hospital spokeswoman lynn mcmahon 
stormie was listed as critical sunday afternoon but was 
upgraded to critical but stable after she was taken off a 
respirator about 7 pm and was breathing on her own ms mcmahon 
said 
she had been placed back on a respirator friday after fluid 
began collecting in her lungs 
stormie received her second liver transplant a week ago tuesday 
she returned to the operating room the next day when doctors 
operated to halt internal bleeding 
her first transplant in 1984 was needed to control effects of 
a rare disease that left her cholesterol levels 10 times greater 
than normal the second operation resulted from permanent liver 
damage caused by hepatitis 
her donor heart has remained healthy doctors said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

