<TEXT>
a man who saw his companion die in a hail of 
bullets allegedly fired by a drug gang was himself slain earlier 
this month apparently to make sure he did not testify against 
those accused in the womans murder according to a published 
report 
john shelton 43 was gunned down feb 7 by a riflebearing 
skimasked killer who police believe was a hired hit man the new 
york times reported in tuesday editions quoting unidentified 
investigators 
shelton had witnessed the death of maxine peterson who was hit 
by gunfire nearly two years ago as she stood holding her baby in 
the kitchen of her home in the new york city borough of queens 
shelton had been living with ms peterson at the time 
he was to testify in the trial of ms petersons accused 
murderers which began monday in state supreme court in queens the 
prosecution and the defense presented opening statements without 
mentioning shelton 
michael bethea 18 was indicted in sheltons murder 
on trial in ms petersons murder are gary steadman 24 kevin 
gaines 27 raymond blair 21 and keenan wynn 21 
sheltons murder is apparently the latest case of a witness 
being murdered or menaced in queens mildred greene 61 a 
dispatcher for a car service was shot to death in 1987 after 
testifying before a grand jury about a gun battle that took place 
outside the car service office 
in another case the home of a guyanese immigrant was firebombed 
twice after he complained about drug dealers a police officer 
edward byrne was later murdered while he guarded the house 
</TEXT>
