<TEXT>
a youth driving a car he won for being 
named the nations safest teenage driver may have fallen asleep at 
the wheel before he and another driver were killed in a twocar 
accident police said 
a car driven by michael doucette 17 of concord drifted over 
the center line and slammed into one being driven by sharon ann 
link 19 of lebanon according to police reports 
both were pronounced dead at the scene friday evening 
police said it appeared link may have tried to swerve out of the 
way before the collision in the extreme right side of her lane 
preliminary investigation shows doucette may have fallen 
asleep at the wheel the police report said 
a passenger in the link vehicle was in stable condition sunday 
at concord hospital 
last july doucette won the safe driving title in a contest 
called operation driver excellence sponsored by dodge and 
amvets a veterans group 
he won a 5000 scholarship a trophy and the use for a year of 
an 1989 dodge the car he was driving friday 
doucette driving the winning car was one of the attractions in 
a new years eve parade down concords main street 
concord high school principal charles foley was shaken by the 
news he was just a fine kid from a good family foley said 
its heartbreaking 
after winning the competition last year doucette said the 
contest was like a drivers test only a lot harder 
