a bomb exploded at an army recruiting 
office in this town northwest of london five days after a similar 
attack in central england for which the ira claimed responsibility 
police said today 
police in west yorkshire about 200 miles northwest of london 
said the recruiting office was empty at the time of the blast 
sunday night they said the blast damaged the front door and a 
window but injured no one 
no one claimed responsibility for that attack 
on tuesday a bomb injured two people in the central england 
town of leicester when it went off under an army vehicle which had 
just driven away from a recruiting office 
the outlawed irish republican army later said it planted the 
leicester bomb 
after that explosion commander george churchillcoleman head 
of scotland yards antiterrorist squad warned military personnel 
and people in public life to beware of bombings in mainland britain 
by the ira which is fighting to end british rule in northern 
ireland 
in september an ira bomb killed 10 members of a band at the 
marine barracks in deal in southeast england 
