leaders said they saw no need to add poland to the group of four 
nations that will discuss reunification with the two german states 
poland like east germany has abandoned its communist monopoly 
government 
the allies which defeated germany in world war ii the united 
states soviet union great britain and france have agreed to 
convene meetings that are likely to lead to a unified germany 
perhaps as soon as this year 
bush and kohl fielded questions from reporters for nearly an 
hour in a recreation hall at camp greentop just down the road from 
camp david atop the catoctin mountains of maryland 
kohl said west germany had proven its commitment to democracy in 
the last 40 years as a loyal and reliable partner in human rights 
and the defense of freedom he said he had put his own political 
existence on the line in supporting the deployment of us pershing 
missiles in west germany in 1983 
kohl also noted that he favors the political union of europe 
and ceding more authority to the european parliament 
in other words we want this united germany to be ever more 
embedded in an integration process with its neighbors so nobody 
needs to be afraid said kohl 
