23monthold evan tsao in the july 19 crash of united flight 232 in 
an iowa cornfield 
the boys mother sylvia tsao survived the crash while the 
toddler died of smoke inhalation proponents of the seat rule say 
he might have lived if hed been strapped in next to his mother 
a harvard medical school study in the early 1980s estimated that 
three infants might be saved over five years if all children used 
safety seats on airliners no group has come up with statistics on 
injuries to unsecured infants 
