demanding radical political and economic reforms 
a resolution passed by a show of demonstrators hands and a 
resounding da said the president should be chosen by the 
people not the party apparatus and urged voters in russian 
parliamentary elections next sunday to vote in prodemocracy 
candidates and tear power from the apparatus 
in february 1917 we started on the road to democracy in 
october we got dictatorship now there is a similar situation 
ilya konstantinov a candidate for parliament told the crowd 
outside the lenin sportsconcert complex 
leningrad the site of three uprisings while it was capital of 
the russian empire has been dubbed the cradle of revolution 
in 1905 czarist forces fired on demonstrators demanding democratic 
reforms in a clash known as bloody sunday 
sunday was the anniversary of another uprising the 1917 
february revolution in which bourgeoisdemocratic forces seized 
power and forced czar nicholas ii to abdicate the bolshevik 
communists led by vladimir i lenin took over eight months later 
an hour before the rally at the sports complex about a dozen 
activists in the democratic union a radical group fighting to end 
the communist partys hold on power gathered on a square 
as about 100 police surrounded the crowd and kgb plainclothes 
agents stood by an officer shouted through a megaphone that no 
demonstration was authorized 
a dozen riot police wearing white helmets and green bulletproof 
vests then dragged away several of the activists who had no 
protest posters and had not made any public statements 
the activists were loaded onto buses for detention a 
parliamentary candidate and associated press photographer dominique 
mollard also were taken away but later released after their 
identification documents were checked 
one activist climbed atop a yellow construction crane and 
unfurled a cloth banner that referred to next sundays elections 
boycott its your first step to freedom it read 
five riot police mounted the crane and dragged down the 
protester 
leaders of the peoples front leningrads biggest prodemocracy 
group decided to boycott the authorized rally because they feared 
retaliation from either the government or rightwing groups 
but dissenting peoples front members showed up and harshly 
condemned their leaders decision 
writer mikhail chulaky a peoples front member told the crowd 
that the communist partys decision earlier this month to end its 
monopoly on power was overdue and added the party of genocide 
must be disbanded like germanys nazi party was disbanded by 
nuremberg 
under stalin thousands of political opponents were murdered 
several speakers attacked president mikhail s gorbachevs 
proposal to strengthen his powers as president again they are 
