<TEXT>
the human rights situation in romania has improved 
markedly since the revolution that toppled nicolae ceausescu but 
fear suspicion and distrust linger on according to a un report 
released today 
the report mentioned death threats against politicians and wide 
concern that the securitate ceausescus repressive secret police 
may be still active although the new leadership says it has been 
disbanded 
it also said the problem of ethnic minorities in romania will 
require close examination and adequate measures and that the 
launching and distribution of printed media is not yet fully 
assured 
the report was compiled by swiss jurist joseph voyame under a 
1988 mandate from the 43nation un human rights commission 
voyame spent five days in romania earlier this month on an 
invitation from the new leadership 
he was barred from romania while ceausescu held power and a 
first report based on sources outside romania was dated dec 18 
shortly before the dictator was deposed and later executed 
his frenchlanguage update prepared for the un commissions 
current session said human rights in romania have not yet been 
fully restored but that the situation has considerably 
improved it stated however the climate of suspicion and 
fear that prevailed under ceausescu was likely to vanish only 
gradually 
in the meantime the manipulation of public opinion remains to 
be feared the report said 
voyame cited testimony that a member of the national peasants 
party was slain in the town of bacau and that there were several 
cases of violent death among members of the hungarian minority 
in the report voyame said he was also informed that a critic of 
the national salvation front the new leadership was killed in a 
car accident under circumstances that are still unclear 
in addition to these signs of physical violence certain 
measures of psychological intimidation are said to continue he 
said numerous persons have informed the special investigator of 
death threats against themselves against members of their 
families or against people they know 
voyame said witnesses from nonofficial circles criticized the 
fact that there is no precise information on how the problem of the 
securitate has been resolved 
</TEXT>
