the fact that for the first time in history we now have national 
education goals and objectives 
the six goals set for the year 2000 were set forth by bush in 
his state of the union address and endorsed over the weekend by the 
governors at their annual midwinter meeting 
were launching a new era in education reform the president 
said its focus high expectations its hallmark results 
gov booth gardner of washington vice chairman of the national 
governors association said the goals would changes the nations 
schools from being a place where people have an opportunity to 
learn to a place where we ensure that all students will learn 
