thoroughbred breeders may lift a skeptical eyebrow but 
according to the association the versatile american quarter horse 
is 
skilled in disciplines ranging from cattle cutting to polo 
unequaled as a racehorse in sprint distances the horse got 
its name from its burst of speed in quartermile races down the 
dirt streets of early settlements 
the quickest horse in the world quarter horses are renowned 
for their lightning getaways bursting from a starting gate to 45 
mph in three strides 
the worlds finest roping reining and cutting horse 
the nations most popular breed and the only breed indigenous 
to this country 
the quarter horse even helped win the old west the real one 
not hollywoods version 
id agree with all those things said benny scott of fort 
worth former owner and publisher of quarter horse racing but if 
