brisk exports and heavy domestic use are 
draining off us cotton inventories and boosting prices the 
agriculture department said monday 
domestic mills used 78 million bales in 198889 the 
departments economic research service said in a preliminary report 
this season strong denim demand and apparel sales are 
expected to push consumption to 82 million bales the highest in 
nearly two decades the report said mill use for the first six 
