supreme council on friday to ban communist cells at the workplace 
postpone general elections from may to june the opposition had 
sought a delay until november to give it time to prepare and call 
foreign observers to monitor the voting 
while professing a commitment to democracy the communist party 
is in sole control of government and appears less willing to 
compromise with opposition forces than sister parties in soviet 
bloc countries further on the path to pluralism 
participants at the monday rally said the opposition planned to 
continue to organize such demonstrations as a way to pressure the 
communist party into accepting its demands for full democracy at 
talks between the two sides that opened in early january 
also monday a congress of the bulgarian communist youth union 
