pennsylvania and new jersey as well as the city of philadelphia 
allegheny county pa and the district of columbia 
this is a good initiative said maryland gov william donald 
schaefer the regulations in one state should be as similar as 
possible to those in the next state 
representatives of each state will meet tuesday to begin 
deciding how to develop consistent policies on acid rain as well as 
on emissions of ozone toxic chemicals and volatile organic 
chemicals that send vapors into the air 
already delaware maryland and new jersey have laws restricting 
the vapors emitted by gasoline similar legislation is pending in 
pennsylvania and philadelphia according to phillip retallnick 
director of delawares division of air and waste management 
schaefer suggested the idea of regional cooperation could be 
extended to other environmental issues he said midatlantic 
governors might join forces on plastics recycling while virginia 
gov douglas wilder said he could foresee them acting together to 
solve problems of solidwaste disposal 
</TEXT>
