emergency in a third of the nation giving the military broad 
powers to fight leftist guerrillas 
the measure affects eight departments apurimac ayacucho 
huancavelica junin pasco huanuco san martin and ucayali and 
one province ucayali in loreto department peru is divided into 24 
departments which are subdivided into provinces 
the areas are in the central and southern highlands and northern 
jungle 
the state of emergency puts the areas under military control and 
suspends individual rights such as unrestricted travel protection 
against arrest without a judicial order and prohibition against 
violation of residences without search warrants 
lima perus capital and home to a third of its 22 million 
people also is under a state of emergency but it is administered 
by the national police 
