a small earthquake shook the 
eastern slope of the sierra nevada on monday morning no damage was 
immediately reported 
seismologists at california institute of technology in pasadena 
registered the 717 am temblor at 35 on the richter scale while 
the united states geological service at menlo park had a 39 
reading 
the epicenter was 17 miles southeast of mammoth lakes and 20 
miles westnorthwest of bishop 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 
