miami said prosecutors also are battling secretiveness 
we have intelligence agencies saying we know you have to try 
your case but youre not going to do it with our stuff 
complained mcadams 
on the other hand he said defense attorneys are trying to push 
the prosecution in an attempt to force the government to drop 
charges to avoid revealing secrets 
hoeveler noting the classifiedinformation complications said 
he hoped the trial would begin in november but said it would start 
no later than january 1991 
the judge also heard arguments by attorneys for the four 
remaining noriega codefendants in custody or out on bond 
requesting separate trials 
but prosecutors insisted the five be tried together 
hoeveler said he would rule later on the outstanding secrecy 
issues and the requests for separate trials 
a sixth defendant panamanian pilot eduardo pardo has pleaded 
guilty to flying drug proceeds from fort lauderdale to panama he 
has not been sentenced ten more defendants including medellin 
cartel boss pablo escobar gaviria remain at large 
