five sets of remains belonging to vietnamera 
servicemen have been identified by the armys central 
identification laboratory the us pacific command said monday 
the remains of navy cmdr frank c elkins of bladenboro nc 
who was lost in north vietnam on oct 12 1966 were among 28 
repatriated by vietnam on june 21 1989 nine of those remains have 
been identified 
the other four americans were among 25 repatriated on jan 23 
1989 seven of those remains have been identified 
three of the remains all army soldiers lost in south vietnam on 
dec 2 1969 were identified as chief warrant officer william c 
dunlap of tucson ariz chief warrant officer martin d vanden 
eykel ii of wheaton ill and staff sgt william d sanderlin of 
fort worth texas 
the name of the fifth serviceman was withheld at the request of 
his family the army said 
the remains were scheduled to leave hickam air force base here 
for travis air force base calif on tuesday to begin their final 
journey home 
