todays highlight in history 
on march 9 1989 the senate rejected president bushs 
nomination of john tower to be defense secretary the 5347 vote 
was the first time in 30 years that a president was denied his 
choice of a cabinet member 
also one year ago eastern airlines filed for bankruptcy 
protection in a bid to conserve cash and gain time to persuade 
striking employees to return to work 
