<TEXT>
 
rigoletto opera in three acts by giuseppe verdi a two cd 
album london riccardo chailly conductor 
 
this recording of what many consider verdis breakthrough 
opera from his youthful period into a more mature style has a 
bright sound a thoughtful conductor riccardo chailly and about 
the best cast that could be assembled today 
by coincidence the three principals are the same singers who 
have just completed a series of rigolettos in a new production 
at the metropolitan opera house 
luciano pavarotti is in fine form as the womanizing scoundrelly 
duke a role he has been singing better than anyone else for two 
decades illadvised ventures into heavier parts have robbed him of 
some of the unforced freshness he had in his youth but pavarotti 
is still a model of stylishness and opulent sound he even musters 
a high eflat for the climax of his act 2 cabaletta possenti 
amor mi chiama 
as gilda the betrayed maiden who sacrifices her life for this 
cad soprano june anderson shows why she has generated such 
excitement in the operatic world of late she displays dazzling 
purity of tone all the way up to high e but more impressively she 
has a fullsize dramatic voice not the pipsqueak coloratura one 
often hears in this part comparisons with joan sutherland may be 
premature but one is eager to hear more 
in the title role baritone leo nucci sounds better than he did 
in live performance probably because the studio recording helps 
amplify a voice of only medium strength his interpretation is 
always interesting and often moving he seems to be living the 
character not just singing the notes 
as a bonus two relatively minor parts are cast with unusual 
strength bass nicolai ghiaurov sounds appropriately sepulchral as 
the hired assassin sparafucile and mezzo shirley verrett brings 
her usual regal presence to the part of his sister the sultry 
maddalena just to make it clear miss verrett is no supporting 
player the album carries a special note stating that she agreed 
to make a cameo appearance as a special favor to mr pavarotti 
chailly conducts the orchestra and chorus of the teatro comunale 
di bologna 
by mike silverman associated press writer 
</TEXT>
