<TEXT>
so whats so unusual about a german director 
and a german star making a film in stuttgart well it happens to 
be stuttgart ark 
the movie is rosalie goes shopping another collaboration of 
the idiosyncratic filmmaker percy adlon and his favorite actress 
marianne saegebrecht she recently was in los angeles to talk about 
how the film came about 
percy was making a trip from the east coast to the west coast 
and he came upon a place called stuttgart arkansas he found this 
very precious little city with its interesting buildings and 
factory and he saw this plane circling around he found the 
airport and he talked to the pilot and to his wife she said 
that was the beginning of the story having made a lot of 
documentaries he likes to use real people and real places 
adlon and cowriter christopher doherty devised a fanciful tale 
of an arkansas cropduster brad davis his german wife and their 
large brood to keep her family in luxuries the wife plays her 
credit cards with the skill of a las vegas blackjack dealer she 
breaks all the monetary laws plus the criminal code but amasses 
enough credit for a leveraged buyout 
when percy came to me with the script first i was shocked 
saegebrecht said i couldnt imagine playing this strong woman 
with a big ego and shes stealing and doing this and that i said 
no this is not for me 
percy said i wrote it for you you are in my mind because i 
discovered there is another part of you i said no he said 
think about it 
i was still against it i dont have to lie i dont have to 
steal i dont have the bad motherrelationship that she has but 
then i went into her background of why she wanted to get as far 
away from home as possible also when i went to arkansas i 
understood her much better 
adlon often gets his way with the actress though not always 
theirs is a symbiotic relationship that resulted in sugarbaby 
in 1984 and bagdad cafe in 1987 the director has remarked 
there is no facet of mariannes face which is not alluring when 
caught by the camera and she doesnt even realize it 
indeed saegebrecht seems ingenuous about her success though 
she retains the confidence of an experienced actress she is stout 
but moves like a petite woman her english comes in spurts with 
occasional transpositions of german rhetoric 
rosalie goes shopping continues her education in things 
american it began with visits to new york pennsylvania and los 
angeles then moved to the southwestern desert for the filming of 
bagdad cafe arkansas was a revelation 
the middle west my god what a difference she exclaimed 
there is a village and then it is very far to the next village 
the restaurants are closing at 9 its not allowed to drink 
alcohol it is allowed to buy it then they hide it in a bag all 
these things are completely different 
and its a mans mans mans world they all have guns not 
only one gun two guns three guns when you go on the highway all 
the cars coming by theres a gun in the window they like to hunt 
we were there during squirrel hunting later its duck hunting time 
but also i met beautiful people i walked around they were 
shocked that i would they were very communicative and helpful 
saegebrecht was born in starnberg bavaria in 1945 and started 
in show business by managing a cabaret revue with her thenhusband 
in 1977 she concocted something she called opera curiosa a 
touring revue with a cast including ballet dancers strip teasers 
clowns musclemen street singers and opera performers 
adlon cast her first in a television drama followed with a 
feature film the swing her appearances in his films have 
caught the attention of american filmmakers paul mazursky cast her 
in moon over parador and danny devito gave her a role with 
himself kathleen turner and michael douglas in the war of the 
roses 
more hollywood movies 
maybe so she said but my home will always be in munich 
</TEXT>
