<TEXT>
forbes magazine is the cornerstone of a forbes 
family empire that ranges from publishing to collections of faberge 
eggs a moroccan palace a south pacific island and acres of 
colorado ranchland 
malcolm s forbes made it all work in tandem through force of 
personality 
publishing executives and analysts said forbes magazine lost its 
its best salesman this past weekend with the death of its chairman 
and editor in chief 
forbes sojourns by motorcycle and hot air balloon through 
exotic locales and his lavish parties attended by heads of state 
celebrities and corporate bosses undoubtedly helped create 
excitement about his flagship magazine 
im sure that trickled down to advertising orders said 
magazine publishing consultant martin walker 
media analyst john reidy agreed that forbes style helped in a 
major way to bring in advertisers there was probably nobody quite 
like that before 
but the analysts said forbes also left behind a strong 
organization in which he gave increasing responsibility to his 
designated successor his oldest son malcolm forbes jr known as 
steve and that the company should thrive 
malcolm jr who has won four awards for economic forecasting 
from usx corp announced sunday he would take over as chairman and 
chief executive of the magazine and the familyowned company and as 
editor in chief of forbes 
three other forbes sons also have roles with the company 
while the death of malcolm forbes is a loss to journalism and 
certainly to the company he did so much to build one can fully 
anticipate that that his company will continue to do very well 
said marshall loeb managing editor of fortune a key competitor to 
forbes magazine 
forbes magazine was started two years before malcolm forbes was 
born 
his father scottish immigrant bertie charles forbes was a 
syndicated financial journalist for a new york newspaper and 
launched forbes in 1917 
malcolm forbes born aug 19 1919 became associate publisher 
of the magazine in 1947 when bc forbes died he was succeeded by 
his oldest son bruce and malcolm moved up to the posts of editor 
and publisher 
bruce died in 1964 and malcolm took the top jobs the magazine 
had about 800 ad pages a year and a circulation of 100000 at his 
death ad pages were over 3900 and circulation exceeded 735000 
forbes made his fathers magazine unique among the business 
magazines by providing a more personalized view of business 
than fortune and business week did according to the magazine 
analyst walker 
the magazine focused more on the strategies of individual 
entrepreneurs and corporate leaders rather than daytoday business 
news its big annual list was not of the top companies like the 
fortune 500 but the wealthiest 400 american individuals and 
families 
he forced the others to address business in a more human and 
personal way walker said fortunes loeb said he shook us all 
up 
last year the biweekly forbes ad pages were slightly ahead of 
the biweekly fortune at 3775 pages but behind the weekly business 
week at 4914 pages according to publishers information bureau 
figures for 1989 
