iacocca 
he was the quintessential american optimistic buoyant and 
lots of fun said kissinger 
forbes was born in englewood nj on aug 19 1919 two years 
after his father scottish emigrant bertie charles forbes founded 
forbes magazine 
he graduated from princeton in 1941 then published two weekly 
newspapers in ohio for a year he enlisted in the army in 1942 was 
wounded in combat and received the bronze star and purple heart 
forbes won a seat on the borough council in bernardsville nj 
in 1949 he served in the state senate from 1951 to 1957 and ran 
for governor of new jersey in 1957 losing to robert b meyner 
after his fathers death in 1954 he became publisher and editor 
in chief of forbes the biweekly magazine which offered a more 
personalized account of business news than its competitors rode 
the 1980s bull market and the probusiness reagan era to the 
greatest success since its founding 
experts valued the companys flagship magazine as high as 600 
million while its american heritage magazine suburban newspaper 
real estate and art holdings almost add 100 million or more 
he was a hell of a competitor and a promotional genius said 
stephen shepard editor in chief of business week magazine 
he was a worthy competitor certainly tough charming very 
very effective said marshall loeb managing editor of fortune 
he was unique and larger than life as a journalist 
entrepreneur and human being said warren h phillips chairman 
and chief executive of dow jones amp co which publishes the wall 
street journal 
malcolm forbes jr will succeed his father as chairman and chief 
executive of forbes inc and editor in chief of forbes magazine 
he formerly was president and chief operating officer of forbes 
inc and deputy editor in chief 
father pop always looked to the future said malcolm jr 
he wanted this to remain a family business and it shall as he 
wished and as the family wishes i will succeed him as chief 
executive we will continue to move ahead as he was doing 
