<TEXT>
malcolm forbes had strong opinions on most 
matters of policy and style and the perfect vehicle to flaunt them 
his wit and breezy writing style were displayed in the fact and 
comment section that led each issue of his magazine there forbes 
gave a highly personal account of everything from the key business 
and political issues of the day to pop culture favorite books and 
restaurants 
in the latest issue dated march 5 forbes opined that fiber 
optics and satellite technology were likely to overcome cable 
television urged the establishment of national standards on 
education to help the united states compete with japan and europe 
and applauded president bush for his personal diplomacy with major 
world leaders 
he may sound more cautious than those impressed by dramatic 
hipshooting would like but we are mighty fortunate that in 
situations of international inflammability he knows to whom to 
talk and knows what hes talking about 
forbes also put in a plug for his own personal diplomacy the 
lending of nine of his 12 faberge eggs to a kremlin exhibition 
carried to the heart of communist power aboard his own boeing 727 
emblazoned capitalist tool 
it is the first time in my life that i have really been 
wholeheartedly rooting for the stability and survival of the 
russian government as presently constituted at the least for the 
duration of the exhibit he wrote 
forbes spiced up his column with a sprinkling of witticisms 
which were collected in two volumes the most recent being the 
further sayings of chairman malcolm in 1986 
he had plenty of advice for his magazines target audience the 
nations corporate managers 
he who has the wheel determines the direction 
in management the staid seldom stay long 
if you have no critics you likely have no successes 
attention is to people what fertilizer is to flowers 
he also wrote frequently on wealth suggesting that anyone who 
strived hard could achieve it but that wealth alone didnt give a 
persons true measure 
money seldom changes people it just makes them more visible 
subtract a persons material worth and whats left is his real 
worth 
to be free one must have bread 
alchemy isnt a myth attitude and action can turn anyone and 
anything golden 
but some of his more memorable quips dealt simply with living 
something forbes sought to do in great style 
for enhancing any meal the only thing that beats good wine is 
a better one come to think of it even a poor one is better than 
none at all 
style is one thing fashion usually quite another 
if you dont enjoy the climb giving what it takes to get to 
the top isnt worth it 
criticizing doers is far less fun than doing 
as you get older dont slow down speed up theres less 
time left 
ironically his most recent book they went thataway 
described the extraordinary exits as he put it of 175 famous 
historical figures 
forbes said he wanted to satisfy an oftexpressed curiosity on 
the part of us the living when some wellknown name pops up in 
conversation how many times have we said whatever became of 
himher 
he denied having any morbid fascination with death itself 
though 
since its lifes only certainty and since being against it 
isnt apt to affect the result dwelling on death strikes me as a 
woeful wanton waste of time he wrote 
it seems to me life is for the living 
</TEXT>
