last year it bottomed out in may 
last week the rig count increased for the first time in 1990 
when it jumped by 19 rigs to total 918 a year ago the count was 
757 
baker hughes rig count the widely watched industry index of 
drilling activity reflects the number of rotary rigs actively 
exploring for oil and gas as of last friday not the number of 
producing wells 
houstonbased hughes tool co an oil toolmaker company that 
merged with baker international corp of orange calif has kept 
track of the rig count since 1940 
in december 1981 at the height of the oil boom the rig count 
reached a peak of 4500 but oil prices plunged to less than 10 
per 42gallon barrel in the summer of 1986 prompting a collapse in 
the rig count that bottomed out at 663 the lowest since hughes 
began compiling figures 
among major oil producing states texas saw drastic activity for 
the third straight week posting a loss of eight rigs last week it 
gained 16 and slipped by seven the previous week 
oklahoma this week had the biggest decline with 13 after no 
activity last week other states posting losses were california and 
north dakota with one each 
states posting gains for the week included kansas seven 
pennsylvania two and louisiana and wyoming one each 
there were no changes in the number of rigs operating in 
colorado michigan new mexico and ohio 
</TEXT>
