<TEXT>
the supreme court agreed monday to use an 
oklahoma dispute over mortgage insurance to settle the question of 
when a court judgment is final a recurring procedural issue in the 
federal courts 
the justices said they will consider reinstating a suit by 
firstier mortgage co against investors mortgage insurance co 
involving eight mortgage loans on buildings in elk city okla 
firstier accused investors of bad faith in failing to pay off 
insurance claims 
us district judge luther bohanon sitting in oklahoma city 
threw out the suit announcing from the bench on jan 26 1989 that 
the insurance policies were void because of fraud 
firstier then asked the 10th us circuit court of appeals to 
overrule the judge and revive the suit 
the appeals court said last september that the judges oral 
announcement was not a final decision and therefore the appeals 
court did not have authority over the case 
in appealing to the supreme court firstier said the judges 
ruling from the bench disposed of all claims in the case and should 
be considered a final decision 
all that remained was for the judge to put the details in 
writing and the lack of a written opinion should not make the 
appeal premature firstier argued 
the company said the 10th circuit court ruling is in conflict 
with rulings by other federal appeals courts 
the case is firstier mortgage vs investors mortgage insurance 
891063 
