mouse joined the company in 1945 as an announcement and 
promotion director at whioam in dayton the first broadcasting 
property of the companys founder the late gov james m cox of 
ohio in 1969 mouse was elected a corporate vice president of cox 
communications inc a public company that later merged with the 
private cox enterprises 
he became president of the broadcasting division in 1987 
cox enterprises also owns newspapers including the atlanta 
journal and constitution and cable television stations 
